# Cursor Rules for React Native + Expo

This configuration instructs Cursor to follow React Native and Expo best practices for mobile app development.

## 1. Core Principles
- **Framework**: React Native with Expo SDK 50+
- **Routing**: Expo Router (file-based routing)
- **Language**: TypeScript strict mode
- **Styling**: StyleSheet API or NativeWind (Tailwind for RN)
- **Components**: Functional components with hooks only
- **UI Library**: React Native Paper, Tamagui, or NativeBase (choose one per project)

## 2. File Structure & Naming
- **Expo Router File Structure**:
    ```
    app/
    ├── (tabs)/             # Tab navigation group
    │   ├── index.tsx       # Home screen
    │   ├── profile.tsx     # Profile screen
    │   └── _layout.tsx     # Tab layout
    ├── modal.tsx           # Modal screen
    ├── [id].tsx            # Dynamic route
    └── _layout.tsx         # Root layout
    components/
    ├── ui/                 # Reusable UI components
    └── shared/             # Shared components
    hooks/                  # Custom hooks
    utils/                  # Utility functions
    ```
- **Naming**:
    - Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `UserCard.tsx`)
    - Screens: `kebab-case.tsx` or `index.tsx` in folders
    - Hooks: `useCamelCase.ts` (e.g., `useAuth.ts`)
    - Utils: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `formatDate.ts`)

## 3. Component Standards
- **Use Functional Components** with TypeScript
- **Destructure Props** in function signature
- **Memo for Performance**: Use `React.memo` for expensive components
- **Hooks**: useState, useEffect, useCallback, useMemo appropriately

## 4. Coding Standards
- **Type Everything**: No `any` types
    ```typescript
    interface UserCardProps {
        user: User;
        onPress?: (userId: string) => void;
    }
    ```
- **Styled Components Pattern**:
    ```typescript
    const styles = StyleSheet.create({
        container: {
            flex: 1,
            padding: 16,
            backgroundColor: '#fff',
        },
        title: {
            fontSize: 20,
            fontWeight: '600',
            color: '#000',
        },
    });
    ```
- **Platform-Specific Code**: Use `Platform.select()`
    ```typescript
    import { Platform } from 'react-native';
    
    const shadowStyle = Platform.select({
        ios: {
            shadowColor: '#000',
            shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 2 },
            shadowOpacity: 0.1,
            shadowRadius: 4,
        },
        android: {
            elevation: 4,
        },
    });
    ```

## 5. Typical Component Template
```typescript
import React, { memo } from 'react';
import { View, Text, TouchableOpacity, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

interface UserCardProps {
    userId: string;
    name: string;
    email: string;
    onPress?: (userId: string) => void;
}

export const UserCard = memo<UserCardProps>(({ 
    userId, 
    name, 
    email, 
    onPress 
}) => {
    const handlePress = () => {
        onPress?.(userId);
    };

    return (
        <TouchableOpacity 
            style={styles.container} 
            onPress={handlePress}
            activeOpacity={0.7}
        >
            <Text style={styles.name}>{name}</Text>
            <Text style={styles.email}>{email}</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
    );
});

UserCard.displayName = 'UserCard';

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
    container: {
        padding: 16,
        backgroundColor: '#fff',
        borderRadius: 12,
        marginBottom: 12,
        shadowColor: '#000',
        shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 2 },
        shadowOpacity: 0.1,
        shadowRadius: 4,
        elevation: 3,
    },
    name: {
        fontSize: 18,
        fontWeight: '600',
        color: '#1a1a1a',
        marginBottom: 4,
    },
    email: {
        fontSize: 14,
        color: '#666',
    },
});
```

## 6. Navigation with Expo Router
- **File-based routing**: Use file names for routes
- **Typed routes**: Use `Href` type from expo-router
- **Navigation**: Use `router.push()`, `router.back()`, etc.

```typescript
import { router, Href } from 'expo-router';

// Navigate to a screen
router.push('/profile');

// Navigate with params
router.push({
    pathname: '/user/[id]',
    params: { id: '123' }
} as Href);

// Go back
router.back();
```

## 7. State Management
- **Local State**: useState for component-level state
- **Global State**: 
    - Zustand (recommended for simplicity)
    - React Context + useReducer
    - Redux Toolkit (for complex apps)

```typescript
// Zustand store example
import { create } from 'zustand';

interface AuthStore {
    user: User | null;
    isAuthenticated: boolean;
    login: (user: User) => void;
    logout: () => void;
}

export const useAuthStore = create<AuthStore>((set) => ({
    user: null,
    isAuthenticated: false,
    login: (user) => set({ user, isAuthenticated: true }),
    logout: () => set({ user: null, isAuthenticated: false }),
}));
```

## 8. Data Fetching
- **Use TanStack Query (React Query)** for API calls
- **Async Storage**: For local persistence (not secure storage)
- **Expo SecureStore**: For sensitive data (tokens, credentials)

```typescript
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import * as SecureStore from 'expo-secure-store';

// API fetch with React Query
export const useUser = (userId: string) => {
    return useQuery({
        queryKey: ['user', userId],
        queryFn: async () => {
            const response = await fetch(`/api/users/${userId}`);
            if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Failed to fetch user');
            return response.json();
        },
    });
};

// Secure storage
const saveToken = async (token: string) => {
    await SecureStore.setItemAsync('authToken', token);
};

const getToken = async () => {
    return await SecureStore.getItemAsync('authToken');
};
```

## 9. Performance Optimization
- **FlatList for Lists**: Never use `.map()` for long lists
    ```typescript
    <FlatList
        data={users}
        keyExtractor={(item) => item.id}
        renderItem={({ item }) => <UserCard user={item} />}
        initialNumToRender={10}
        maxToRenderPerBatch={10}
        windowSize={5}
    />
    ```
- **Image Optimization**: Use Expo Image
    ```typescript
    import { Image } from 'expo-image';
    
    <Image
        source={{ uri: imageUrl }}
        style={styles.image}
        contentFit="cover"
        transition={200}
    />
    ```
- **useMemo and useCallback**: Prevent unnecessary re-renders
    ```typescript
    const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => 
        computeExpensiveValue(data), 
        [data]
    );
    
    const handlePress = useCallback(() => {
        onItemPress(item.id);
    }, [item.id, onItemPress]);
    ```

## 10. Native Features
- **Camera**: Use `expo-camera` or `expo-image-picker`
- **Location**: Use `expo-location`
- **Notifications**: Use `expo-notifications`
- **Permissions**: Always request before accessing native features

```typescript
import * as Location from 'expo-location';

const requestLocationPermission = async () => {
    const { status } = await Location.requestForegroundPermissionsAsync();
    
    if (status !== 'granted') {
        Alert.alert('Permission denied', 'Location access is required');
        return;
    }
    
    const location = await Location.getCurrentPositionAsync({});
    return location;
};
```

## 11. Error Boundaries
- **Wrap screens in error boundaries**
- **Use expo-error-reporter** for production

```typescript
import { ErrorBoundary } from 'react-error-boundary';

function ErrorFallback({ error, resetErrorBoundary }: { error: Error; resetErrorBoundary: () => void }) {
    return (
        <View style={styles.errorContainer}>
            <Text>Something went wrong:</Text>
            <Text>{error.message}</Text>
            <Button title="Try again" onPress={resetErrorBoundary} />
        </View>
    );
}

export default function App() {
    return (
        <ErrorBoundary FallbackComponent={ErrorFallback}>
            <RootNavigator />
        </ErrorBoundary>
    );
}
```

## 12. Testing
- **Jest + React Native Testing Library**
- **Test user interactions, not implementation**

```typescript
import { render, fireEvent } from '@testing-library/react-native';
import { UserCard } from './UserCard';

test('calls onPress when pressed', () => {
    const onPress = jest.fn();
    const { getByText } = render(
        <UserCard 
            userId="1" 
            name="John Doe" 
            email="john@example.com" 
            onPress={onPress} 
        />
    );
    
    fireEvent.press(getByText('John Doe'));
    expect(onPress).toHaveBeenCalledWith('1');
});
```

## 13. Styling Best Practices
- **Use constants for colors, spacing, fonts**
    ```typescript
    // constants/theme.ts
    export const Colors = {
        primary: '#6366f1',
        background: '#ffffff',
        text: '#1a1a1a',
        error: '#ef4444',
    } as const;
    
    export const Spacing = {
        xs: 4,
        sm: 8,
        md: 16,
        lg: 24,
        xl: 32,
    } as const;
    ```
- **Responsive Design**: Use Dimensions or react-native-size-matters
    ```typescript
    import { Dimensions } from 'react-native';
    
    const { width, height } = Dimensions.get('window');
    
    const styles = StyleSheet.create({
        container: {
            width: width * 0.9,
            padding: width > 768 ? 24 : 16, // Tablet vs Phone
        },
    });
    ```

## 14. Forbidden Patterns
❌ **No class components**  
❌ **No inline styles** (except dynamic values)  
❌ **No `.map()` for long lists** (use FlatList)  
❌ **No `any` types**  
❌ **No unhandled promises**  
❌ **No direct state mutations**
